                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    {{!-- Nature Moves --}}
                    <div class="resource-item-card">
                        <div class="resource-item-thumbnail">
                            <img src="https://static.wixstatic.com/media/9fa2a3_8cdb6af28bff40e0ade7ae07a6d10b06~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_384,h_400,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_avif,quality_auto/NatureMoves_PNG.png" alt="Nature Moves" loading="lazy">
                            <div class="resource-actions-overlay">
                                <a href="/naturemoves/" class="overlay-download-link">
                                    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                        <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"></path>
                                        <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline>
                                        <line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"></line>
                                    </svg>
                                    Explore More
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="resource-item-content">
                            <h3 class="resource-item-title">Nature Moves</h3>
                            <p class="resource-item-desc">Nature Moves is a resource bank of movement-based activities exploring how everything in nature moves, from leaves to ants.</p>
                            <div class="resource-item-footer">
                                <a href="/naturemoves/" class="single-download-btn" style="background: var(--resources-primary); color: #fff; text-align: center;">
                                    Explore More →
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    {{!-- Nature Strokes --}}
                    <div class="resource-item-card">
                        <div class="resource-item-thumbnail">
                            <img src="{{asset 'carousel/3.jpg'}}" alt="Nature Strokes" loading="lazy">
                            <div class="resource-actions-overlay">
                                <a href="/naturestrokes/" class="overlay-download-link">
                                    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                        <path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"></path>
                                        <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline>
                                        <line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"></line>
                                    </svg>
                                    Explore More
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="resource-item-content">
                            <h3 class="resource-item-title">Nature Strokes</h3>
                            <p class="resource-item-desc">Nature Strokes is an Art and Nature handbook using art as a vibrant medium for learning about nature and vice versa.</p>
                            <div class="resource-item-footer">
                                <a href="/naturestrokes/" class="single-download-btn" style="background: var(--resources-primary); color: #fff; text-align: center;">
                                    Explore More →
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        {{!-- 4. Educator Note Section --}}
        <section class="educator-note-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="educator-note-card" data-reveal>
                    <div class="educator-note-header">
                        <div class="educator-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-cubes"></i>
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="educator-title">Note for Educators</h2>
                    </div>
                    <div class="educator-content">
                        <p>
                            Our learning modules are invitations to explore rich, often-overlooked layers of the natural
                            world.
                            Designed to achieves specific learning goals, each level incorporates stories, observation
                            charts,
                            and group activities that link with existing EVS textbooks. They are structured to nurture a
                            deep sense
                            of wonder for ecosystems that are often teeming with life we miss in our daily lives.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="educator-questions">
                        <span class="questions-title">Questions to Explore</span>
                        <ul class="questions-list">
                            <li>How does this module help achieve our current curriculum goals?</li>
                            <li>Which activity sparked the most curiosity among the students?</li>
                            <li>How can we extend these lessons to our immediate school neighborhood?</li>
                            <li>What new perspectives did students gain about water or movement in nature?</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
            // Scroll Reveal
            const observerOptions = {
                threshold: 0.1,
                rootMargin: '0px 0px -50px 0px'
            };

            const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
                entries.forEach(entry => {
                    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                        entry.target.classList.add('active');
                    }
                });
            }, observerOptions);

            document.querySelectorAll('[data-reveal]').forEach(el => {
                observer.observe(el);
            });
        });
    </script>
    {{/post}}